{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"bind","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"SocketAddressT","kind":"genericParameter"},{"text":">(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"address"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"SocketAddressT","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"allowReuse","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"},{"kind":"text","text":") "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"throws"},{"kind":"text","text":" -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"where"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"SocketAddressT"},{"text":" : ","kind":"text"},{"text":"SocketAddressProtocol","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO21SocketAddressProtocolP","kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketAddressProtocol"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is generally required to bind to a local address before you can"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"receive connections. (See "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_socket_listen()"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_socket_accept()"},{"type":"text","text":" )."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"In certain situations, you may also want to bind a socket that will be","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"used to initiate connections, though this is not normally required."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"socket"},{"type":"text","text":" is a TCP socket, then "},{"code":"allowReuse","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" controls the setting"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of the "},{"code":"SO_REUSEADDR","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" socket option; normally it should be ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":" for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"server sockets (sockets that you will eventually call","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"g_socket_accept()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" on), and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"type":"text","text":" for client sockets. (Failing to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"set this flag on a server socket may cause "},{"code":"g_socket_bind()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to return"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"addressInUse","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" if the server program is stopped and then","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"immediately restarted.)"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"code":"socket","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is a UDP socket, then "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"allowReuse"},{"type":"text","text":" determines whether or"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"not other UDP sockets can be bound to the same address at the same"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"time. In particular, you can have several UDP sockets bound to the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"same address, and they will all receive all of the multicast and"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"broadcast packets sent to that address. (The behavior of unicast","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"UDP packets to an address with multiple listeners is not defined.)","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"When a socket is created it is attached to an address family, but it"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"doesn’t have an address in this family. "},{"code":"g_socket_bind()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" assigns the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"address (sometimes called name) of the socket.","type":"text"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketProtocol"]]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/socketprotocol\/bind(address:allowreuse:)"]}],"metadata":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"bind","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"SocketAddressT","kind":"genericParameter"},{"kind":"text","text":">("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"address"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"SocketAddressT"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"allowReuse","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":") "},{"text":"throws","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" -> "},{"text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"role":"symbol","title":"bind(address:allowReuse:)","extendedModule":"GIO","roleHeading":"Instance Method","externalID":"s:3GIO14SocketProtocolPAAE4bind7address10allowReuseSbqd___SbtKAA0b7AddressC0Rd__lF","symbolKind":"method","modules":[{"name":"GIO"}]},"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketProtocol\/bind(address:allowReuse:)"},"references":{"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/SocketAddressProtocol":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"SocketAddressProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketAddressProtocol","abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GSocketAddress"},{"text":" is the equivalent of","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"man:sockaddr(3type)","isActive":true},{"text":" and its subtypes in the BSD sockets","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"API. This is an abstract class; use [class"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/InetSocketAddress","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"] for"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"internet sockets, or [class"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/UnixSocketAddress"},{"text":"] for UNIX domain sockets.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/gio\/socketaddressprotocol","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"SocketAddressProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","title":"SocketAddressProtocol"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/UnixSocketAddress":{"title":"UnixSocketAddress","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"UnixSocketAddress"}],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/unixsocketaddress","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Support for UNIX-domain (also known as local) sockets, corresponding to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"struct sockaddr_un"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"UnixSocketAddress"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/UnixSocketAddress"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/SocketProtocol/bind(address:allowReuse:)":{"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"bind"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"kind":"genericParameter","text":"SocketAddressT"},{"text":">(","kind":"text"},{"text":"address","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"SocketAddressT","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"allowReuse","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":") "},{"text":"throws","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" -> ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketProtocol\/bind(address:allowReuse:)","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"When a socket is created it is attached to an address family, but it","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"doesn’t have an address in this family. "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_socket_bind()"},{"text":" assigns the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"address (sometimes called name) of the socket."}],"title":"bind(address:allowReuse:)","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/socketprotocol\/bind(address:allowreuse:)"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/InetSocketAddress":{"fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"InetSocketAddress"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/InetSocketAddress","abstract":[{"text":"An IPv4 or IPv6 socket address. That is, the combination of a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[class"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/InetAddress","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"] and a port number."}],"url":"\/documentation\/gio\/inetsocketaddress","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"InetSocketAddress","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","title":"InetSocketAddress"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/SocketProtocol":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketProtocol","title":"SocketProtocol","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/socketprotocol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"code":"GSocket","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is a low-level networking primitive. It is a more or less"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"direct mapping of the BSD socket API in a portable GObject based API.",